description: The Jubilee Greenway was completed in 2012 to mark the Queen's Diamond Jubilee and the London 2012 Games.

texts: {"template":"intro","texts":["The Jubilee Greenway was completed in 2012 to mark the Queen's Diamond Jubilee and the London 2012 Games."],"link":{"image":{}},"image":{},"wrapped":false}
The most recent addition to the Walk London routes, the Jubilee Greenway is 60km long - one km for each year of the Queen's reign, to link together all the major Games sites.

{"template":"bulletlist","items":["Kensington Palace","Little Venice","Chapel Market","Victoria Park","Olympic Park","O2 Arena","Greenwich Park","Peyps Park","HMS Belfast","Shakespeare's Globe Theatre","Buckingham Palace","Regents Park","Camden Market","Beckton District Park","Woolwich Foot Tunnel","Thames Barrier"]}
This route is way-marked by distinctive glass, pavement slabs. The Queen unveiled the one outside Buckingham Palace in February 2012.
